column2: Hy wife and I did test.One pair of Loons on Delta Lake.  The water pump failed on our pontoon boat - no more tests until that is repaired. There was a slight wind from the sw that day.

A beautiful sunny day with North west wind at 8mph.The air temp is 66 degrees and the water temp as measured on my depth finder is 71.8 degrees. One fishing  boat  near the island - otherwise the lake is quiet. My wife Sally assisted me.
My wife and I did the Secchi Test today. The wind was S.W. at 10 to 15 mph. One Loon on the lake- three counting us. Nothing else was stiring. A light cloud cover was forming.
sw wind at 10 mph. My wife and two guests aboard my pontoon. Sky was clear and sunny. one pair of loons and one fishing boat were on the lake with us.
Roger and sally did the sec chi test. Two fishing boats on lake delta. Light breeze from the North.

My wife Sally and I did Secchi Reading. Satellite day- Path 26.  Winds stiff from South at 10  mph.Water temp was 65.3 on boat depth finder. Mostly sunny with some clouds. No activity on Delta Lake- neither people or wildlife. Beautiful day in the Northland and their still are  Blackberries ripening.

Beautiful day. Sunny with a light  S. breeze.  One young Loon appeared along with three Teal. Outside temp is 63 degrees. One fishing boat and I also fished before Secchi test. Panfishfish for supper.
Two non nesting Loons-Very slight west wind- My wife assisted
Beautiful sunny day with a slight S.W. wind. Two boats fishing . No wildlife visible.
Beautiful day on Lake Delta. Very slight wind with plenty of sunshine and a few clouds. One Loon and one fishing boat on the lake long with some people fishing off their dock. Satellite day also.
Cloudy and overcast- Satellite day-Wind calms Noone on lake and no wildlife spotted

A sunny day with some clouds. Slight breeze out of the NW.There were 7 Loons on the lake including the nesting pair who have one chick. Three fishing boats and2 pontoons were also present. My wife assisted me this morning.
A very cloudy day with a East wind. My wife assisted and we saw one Bald Eagle and The local Loons with their chick. Also there is a Mallard with 5 young that we see often.
VERY BREEZY WITH A SW WIND- MY wife Sally assisted me. Female Loon with nearly full grown chick on lake. no other activity around.

A very cloudy day with rain in the forecast. A stiff North east wind made  it hard for the anchor to hold the boat. I worked alone . The adult Loons have left and the little chick is on its own to fly to Florida or wherever. A few Grebes were present- otherwise the lake was was quiet.Today was a satellite day.
4 boats fishing. light ssw wind. one Loon on lake Delta.   My wife sally assisted.
SSW wind at 8 mph. Four fishing boats. One Loon feeding. Sky is overcast. Satellite day for path 26. My wife assisted me.
Light n.w. breeze. One canoeist and one paddleboat on Lake  Delta. My wife assisted me. Visited our new neighbors.
